CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1953, pg. 10, reads: "THE WAM'S WHAM...Pittsburgh's WAM'S whamed Pittsburgh Sunday night when they presented the Joe Louis review, complete with Leonard Reed, pictured here with the lovelies, who is one of the top entertainers in country. Also featured was Delores Parker, song stylist, in this first presentation by the charming group. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven women from WAMS [women's auxiliary to the mortuary fraternity] Club, including one on left wearing halter dress with diagonally striped skirt, surrounding Leonard Reed, in hallway with marble walls, another version
